<pre><code>print sub {
  my $f = shift;
  sub {
    my $f1 = shift;
    $f-&gt;( sub { $f1-&gt;( $f1 )-&gt;( @_ ) } )
  }-&gt;( sub {
    my $f2 = shift;
    $f-&gt;( sub { $f2-&gt;( $f2 )-&gt;( @_ ) } )
  } )
}-&gt;( sub {
  my $h = shift;
  sub {
    my $n = shift;
    return 1 if $n &lt;=1;
    return $n * $h-&gt;($n-1);
  }
})-&gt;(5);
</code></pre>

<p>Everything after 'print' and before the '->(5)' represents the subroutine.
